# Aseprite Viewer Project Roadmap (Started: 2026-02-12)
Current Version: v33 (Stable) - GitHub Uploaded

## [CURRENT STATUS - v38 (Final Roadmap Version)]
- Hybrid Profile System: Independent Player/NPC management.
- Combat: Max 2-stack combo buffering, Dash cancel, Multi-step combo movement.
- Movement: Physics-based movement with adjustable Attack Forward.
- Camera: Vertical offset, Right-drag, Manual/Auto toggle.
- Playback: Full control (Pause, Step, Speed, Refresh).
- Hitbox: Slice visualization with persistent keys (H toggle).
- Watch Mode: Real-time Aseprite monitoring (F5 manual support).
- Juice & VFX: Screen Shake (impact-based), Dash After-images (adjustable).
- Persistence: All physics/VFX settings auto-saved via JSON.
- Layers: Individual layer visibility toggling within Settings.

## [COMPLETED IMPROVEMENTS]
1. WATCH MODE (Completed - v34)
2. HITBOX/SLICE VISUALIZER (Completed - v35)
3. JUICE & VFX (Completed - v36)
4. SETTINGS PERSISTENCE (Completed - v37)
5. LAYER MANAGEMENT (Completed - v38)
   - Screen Shake on heavy hits (Combo 4, Powerbomb).
   - Simple ghosting/after-image effects for Dash.

4. SETTINGS PERSISTENCE:
   - Save/Load physics and camera constants to 'config.json' or 'project_prefs.json'.

5. LAYER MANAGEMENT:
   - Optional layer filtering during export to toggle equipment/visuals.

## [DEVELOPER NOTES]
- All tools/commands must use 'pwsh' (PowerShell 7).
- Maintain minimal chitchat and focus on idiomatic Python/Pygame code.
- Always check 'ase_debug.log' for buffer/export errors.
